author: @sbcinema2363
text: India is waking up technologically!? LOL, bad analysis there. Indians already have a big prevalence in the sciences, engineering, and medical fields. The cliche of the Indian engineer can be seen in the 80's with movies like Short Circuit, with Fischer Stevens playing an Indian inventor of the Johnny 5 robot!  The main reason is twofold:     1) India had a huge population growth rate of ~2% in the 1980-2000 period, that resulted in about 500 million children that will reach adulthood around now, a portion of which are interested in python stuff. That's 1.5x the ENTIRE population of the US! That's the number young adults in India. 1% of that is 500k viewers.    2) English is a big part India languages. Not so in China. If you make a Chinese translated version of your videos, you should see a huge rise in viewrship from there. There is a reason why you see some YouTube reaction channels by non-Indian people cater entirely to watching and reacting to India-centric news and entertainment. The sheer number of views they get are huge!
